MEAN - MongoDB, Express, Angular, Node

MongoDB:
	-NoSQL Document Database
	-Dynamic Structure
	-Binary JSON (format it's saved in)
	-Full index support (query optimization)
	-Map/Reduce  & Aggregation
	-Scale & Availability

	Mongod - run server
	mongo - client
	 user db-name
	 show collections
	 db.db-name.insters({json data})
	 db.db-name.find()

Node.js
-JS on the server
-Google's v8 engine
-Non-blocking asyn model - runs with a single thread
-NPM (Node Package Manager) - installed with Node 
-when installing modules use npm install name --save to add dependencies to package.json file

Express.js
(node module)
 	-web app framework for Node
 	-http server 
 	-routes
 	-middleware - inject

Angular.js
	-client-side MVC framework
	-Build dynamic web apps
	-seperate concerns
	-declarative UI bindings
	-Embeddable (use a little or as much)
	-testable - dependency injections, more maintable

Each projecy contaings a package.json file which holds the project details, *name, *version (bare minimum)
main file 
	- entry point for node server 
	- main.js or server.js 
	- start server: run this file by the command - node filename  node server
	- in code include express